<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML 3.0//EN" "html.dtd">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Employment Placement Services </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<A HREF ="liapp1.htm"></A><BODY>
<center>

<IMG SRC="eps-logo.gif">
</center>
<br>
<i><a href="/lead-inst/epsclips.ram">Listen</a> to real-audio file of recommendations by Tim McConville of the National Right to Work Defense Foundation and Stefan Gleason who found his job though EPS.
</i>
<P>
Founded by Morton C. Blackwell in 1979, the Leadership Institute (LI) actively identifies,
recruits, trains and places principled conservatives in the public policy process.<p>

The Leadership Institute's Free Employment Placement Service is one of the oldest, longest
running, and most successful conservative job banks in Washington. LI's program has placed hundreds of conservatives
in all levels of the public policy process. In addition, its counseling service and educational programs
provide countless other conservatives with the leads, advice and training necessary to succeed in
public policy.<p>

Currently, LI's free Employment Placement Service offers three main placement options.<p>

The main Employment Placement Service program helps conservatives secure full and part-time
work in the public policy, government and private sectors.  A heavy emphasis is placed on filling
positions in Capitol Hill offices, special-interest groups and trade associations. After the 1994 fall election
cycle, special attention was given to Congressional placements and training of prospective Capitol Hill staff.

<p>The Broadcast Media Placement program helps conservatives locate and secure positions in
broadcast and print journalism, as well as public and media relations.<p>

The Intern Placement program helps interested individuals gain experience though
quality internships, volunteer work or temporary positions.<p>

Two full-time placement directors offer career counseling, tips on resume writing, job-hunting,
interviewing techniques, and networking advice to job-seekers.  To set-up an appointment, contact Emily Kertz at (703) 247-2000.<p>

In addition, LI offers a variety of one-day, two-day, three-day, and week-long professional
training programs to help conservatives become effective in the public policy process.<p>

Specialized schools such as the <a href="sc-ch.html">Capitol Hill Staff Training School</a>, the <a href="sc-cd.html">Candidate Development
School</a>, the Foreign Service Opportunity School, and the <a href="sc-brj.html">Broadcast Journalism School</a> teach job-
seekers how to land and succeed in positions within these professions.<p>


Technology-oriented schools including <!--the <a href="sc-yl.html">Youth Leadership School,--></a> the <a href="sc-pr.html">Public Relations

School,</a> the Rhetoric & Campaign Communications School, and
the <a href="sc-sp.html">Student Publications School</a> help conservatives enhance their public policy skills.<p>

<B>To download the LI employment placement services application, click <A HREF="http://www.townhall.com/lead-inst/app.exe">here</A>.<p></B>
<center>The Application file is a 40k Pagemaker 5.0 file.<p>
<Small>(The application is in a self-extracting compressed .exe format.  Once you have saved it to your disk, Run app.exe.</small><P>
<b>

If you are experiencing problems or would like to be sent an application instead, please fill out the  
<br><a href="/lead-inst/epsreq.html">EPS Application Request Form.</a><P></b>
</center>

Further information about LI's free assistance programs for conservative job-seekers can be
obtained from the Director of Employment Placement Services, Emily Kertz, at (703) 247-2000.<p>
